The paper proposes an approach for dense semantic 3D reconstruction, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of potentials over viewing rays and continuous surface area penalization suggests optimization (RO) methods. The paper also mentions the use of a non-convex constraint, which could fall under machine learning (LG) or artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories.
